transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_001
transcriptEntries.text: Hey Jack, how are you doing? How was your first day back after the weekend?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_002
transcriptEntries.text: Good, good. Yeah, feeling refreshed. Ready to dive into this authentication work.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_003
transcriptEntries.text: That's great to hear. So let's talk about the sprint. You picked up the JWT authentication story, which I know is pretty substantial. How are you feeling about the scope?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_004
transcriptEntries.text: I think it's manageable. I've been reading through the JWT spec and some implementation guides. It's definitely more involved than I initially thought, but I think 13 story points is reasonable.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_005
transcriptEntries.text: Okay, that's good. What aspects seem most complex so far?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_006
transcriptEntries.text: Well, the basic token generation seems straightforward. But I'm still wrapping my head around the refresh token flow, especially how to handle token rotation securely. And then there's questions about where to store the tokens, how long they should be valid, that kind of thing.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_007
transcriptEntries.text: Those are exactly the right questions to be asking. Have you had a chance to look at how other services in our ecosystem handle auth?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_008
transcriptEntries.text: A little bit, yeah. I looked at the user service implementation, but it's using a different pattern. It's more session-based rather than JWT-based, so not directly applicable.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_009
transcriptEntries.text: Right, that makes sense. You know, Mike has implemented JWT systems at his previous company. He mentioned earlier today that he's happy to help if you run into architectural decisions. Have you thought about setting up some time with him?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_010
transcriptEntries.text: Yeah, that could be helpful. I don't want to bother him too much since he's got his own work, but maybe once I get a bit further and have more specific questions.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_011
transcriptEntries.text: Jack, you know it's not bothering him, right? That's what the team is for. Collaboration and knowledge sharing. Actually, I think it would be valuable for you to set up time with Mike early, rather than getting stuck later.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_012
transcriptEntries.text: Yeah, you're right. I'll reach out to him this week.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_013
transcriptEntries.text: Great. Now, shifting gears a bit, I also wanted to touch on some team dynamics. Lisa mentioned she might need help with OAuth integration. I noticed you offered to help, which is awesome. How are you feeling about mentoring and knowledge sharing in general?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_014
transcriptEntries.text: Um, it's something I want to get better at. I sometimes feel like I need to make sure I really understand something myself before I can teach it to someone else, you know? I don't want to give bad advice.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_015
transcriptEntries.text: I totally get that, and it shows you care about doing right by your teammates. But you know, sometimes learning together can be just as valuable as having all the answers. And you definitely have enough experience to guide someone who's newer to these concepts.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_016
transcriptEntries.text: That's true. I guess I can at least share what I've learned so far and we can figure out the gaps together.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_017
transcriptEntries.text: Exactly. That's a great mindset. Alright, let's talk about your goals for the rest of this quarter. Beyond the authentication work, what are you hoping to focus on or improve?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_018
transcriptEntries.text: Well, I'd like to get more comfortable with architectural decisions, especially around security. And probably get better at the mentoring thing we just talked about. Maybe contribute more in architecture reviews instead of just listening.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_019
transcriptEntries.text: Those are excellent goals and very much aligned with what I'd love to see from you as a senior engineer. The authentication project is actually a perfect opportunity to work on both of those. You'll be making security decisions, and you could present your approach to the team when you're done.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_020
transcriptEntries.text: Yeah, that makes sense. A kind of knowledge sharing session after I finish the implementation?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_021
transcriptEntries.text: Exactly. And it'll be valuable for the whole team since everyone will need to understand how our auth system works. Alright, I think that covers what I wanted to discuss today. Anything else on your mind?

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_022
transcriptEntries.text: I think I'm good for now. Thanks for the advice about reaching out to Mike early. I'll set something up with him this week.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_023
transcriptEntries.text: Perfect. And remember, I'm always here if you need anything. Have a great rest of your week, Jack.

transcriptEntries.name: conferenceRecords/meet-1on1-sarah-jack-weekly/transcripts/transcript_001/entries/entry_024
transcriptEntries.text: Thanks Sarah, you too. See you tomorrow.
